VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SOMIS; 
</P>
<P>
FIREFIGHTERS PUT OUT 40-ACRE BRUSH FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 100 firefighters extinguished a 40-acre blaze north of Somis Monday 
morning, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Ten fire engines from the Ventura County Fire Department and engines from the 
Santa Paula Fire Department and Camarillo State Hospital responded to the brush 
fire at La Loma Avenue and Price Road at 10:08 p.m. Sunday, Ventura County Fire 
Dispatcher Denis Miller said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire was out by 10:15 a.m. Monday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The investigation into the cause of the fire is continuing, Miller said. CAROL 
WATSON 
</P>
