<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: VISTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Vista mother accused of killing her adopted son had a Jan. 24 preliminary 
hearing date scheduled Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Cheri Mildred Adams, 34, who had pleaded not guilty to a charge of killing 
17-month-old Bryan Adams, made a brief appearance before San Diego Municipal 
Court Judge Larry Stirling with her new attorney, William Rafael. 
</P>
<P>
The boy, who had Down's syndrome, died from an apparent beating on Nov. 27 and 
had multiple bruises on his head and face, according to court records. 
</P>
<P>
The mother called 911 that morning, saying she found her son on the floor face 
down in his bedroom and not breathing. 
</P>
<P>
Her husband, James Adams, 27, was in Honolulu, where he was stationed with the 
Navy. 
</P>
<P>
Adams remains in custody at jail at Las Colinas in Santee in lieu of $250,000 
bail. 
</P>
