<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALOS VERDES 'DREAM HOUSE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Apparently the crux of the homeowner association's position hinges on its bylaw 
that requires anyone building a home in the city to "proceed diligently." 
</P>
<P>
The word proceed means "to go forward," and the word diligent means 
"painstaking, with careful attention to detail." There is no link between the 
phrase "proceed diligently" and time. 
</P>
<P>
The Aughinbaughs could theoretically continue building for another 30 years and 
still be said to be proceeding diligently. 
</P>
<P>
JACK RUSSELL 
</P>
<P>
Downey 
</P>
