REGIONAL EARNINGS: SYNCOR REPORTS SLIGHTLY HIGHER 2ND-QUARTER PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Syncor International Corp., a Chatsworth operator of pharmacy centers that 
primarily serve health-care facilities and doctors, said its fiscal 
second-quarter profit edged up to $1.03 million from $1 million a year earlier, 
when its earnings included a $216,000 tax-related gain. 
</P>
<P>
The latest profit in the quarter that ended Nov. 30 came on a 19% increase in 
Syncor's sales, to $37.3 million from $31.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
For the first half of its fiscal year, Syncor earned $2.10 million, down 
slightly from $2.15 million a year earlier, when Syncor's net income included a 
$548,000 tax gain. Excluding the extraordinary gain, Syncor's profit was up 31% 
from a year ago. Its six-month sales rose 19% to $73.4 million from $61.8 
million. 
</P>
