<TEXT>
<P>
The Valley Industry and Commerce Assn. has merged with the Technology Corridor 
Assn., which promotes clean-air businesses along the Ventura Freeway between 
Woodland Hills and Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
The merger boosts to 300 the membership of the Valley Industry and Commerce 
Assn., founded in 1949 to attract businesses and residents to the San Fernando 
and Santa Clarita valleys and Ventura County. There were 260 members before the 
merger, which was announced Dec. 13. 
