<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Norville News: Ready for more upheaval on the "Today" show? The talk around NBC 
News these days is that "Today's" national correspondent, Katie Couric, will 
take over as the show's co-host when Deborah Norville goes on maternity leave 
next spring. 
</P>
<P>
"She's no substitute -- she's the successor," one NBC News source told TV 
Guide. "Deborah's a bright woman but she doesn't come across that way on 
camera. She comes across as plastic. Katie's real." For the record, Don Browne, 
executive vice president of NBC News, denied that Norville is on the outs. BETH 
KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
