<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and international 
news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rhythm Is Gonna Get Her: Gloria Estefan is back. The singer is returning to 
full speed after spending most of last year recovering from serious back 
injuries suffered in a bus accident. 
</P>
<P>
Her first album since the crash, "Into the Light," will be released Jan. 29. 
The single from the album, "Coming Out of the Dark," is a song inspired by 
Estefan's ordeal. The ballad with gospel influence is due out Jan. 14. Estefan 
will perform at the American Music Awards on Jan. 28, and this spring she'll 
tour Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
