<TEXT>
<P>
Germ Warfare Alert Issued: The federal government wants to know if U.S. 
companies making viruses or bacteria that could be used in germ warfare get any 
unusual requests or evasive answers from prospective foreign buyers. These 
companies "should be alert to . . . approaches by nationals of countries of 
concern (e.g. Iran, Iraq, Syria, and Libya) to enroll as students or to be 
engaged as research workers in courses or projects involving such technical 
data," the Commerce Department advised. 
</P>
<P>
It urged special caution when prospective buyers offer unusually generous 
payments for advice, lie in their answers, ask for unusually strict 
confidentiality or appear to have military links. A notice, published in the 
Federal Register last week, asks companies to call the Commerce Department if 
they run into one of these situations. 
</P>
