<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. SOLDIER DIES IN TRAINING ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EASTERN SAUDI ARABIA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One of five soldiers injured in a training accident last week has died, 
bringing the death toll in Operation Desert Shield to 81, the U.S. military's 
Central Command announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The soldiers from the 3/320th Field Artillery of the 101st Airborne Division 
were participating in a training exercise Thursday when a 105-millimeter 
howitzer exploded, the military said. 
</P>
<P>
One of the soldiers, who had been in a coma, died Sunday, the military said. 
His name was withheld until relatives could be notified. The cause of the 
accident is under investigation. 
</P>
<P>
Two sailors from the aircraft carrier Midway also died Sunday when their tour 
bus overturned on a liberty excursion. the military's Joint Information Bureau 
announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Five other sailors were injured, two seriously, in the accident 50 miles south 
of Al Dhafra air base in Abu Dhabi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
UNITED STATES -- ARMED FORCES -- SAUDI ARABIA; IRAQ -- FOREIGN RELATIONS -- 
KUWAIT; ACCIDENTAL DEATHS -- SAUDI ARABIA; MILITARY MANEUVERS; MILITARY 
CONFRONTATIONS; EXPLOSIONS; CASUALTIES 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122590-0078 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 327134 </DOCID>
