<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEXICO COLD SNAP KILLS 6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONTERREY, Mexico 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A cold snap in northern Mexico claimed six lives over the weekend here in the 
nation's third-largest city. Four of the victims were reported to be children. 
Rescue service spokesman Jose Centeno said the victims froze to death. 
</P>
