<HEADLINE>
<P>
REVELERS WARNED TO DODGE FLYING CORKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A French radio station Monday warned Christmas and New Year revelers to beware 
of flying champagne corks, citing these as a major cause of lost vision. 
</P>
<P>
"Eye trauma by champagne cork is the main cause of eyes lost in this country," 
Radio France-Infos reported in a list of Christmas and New Year safety tips. 
"You aim the bottle in jest at someone near you when opening it and -- pop -- 
off it goes into their eye or into yours." 
</P>
</TEXT>
