CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
TRANSIENT'S DEATH IS RULED SUICIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 20-year-old homeless man, who apparently fashioned a noose from his own 
shoelaces, was found hanged from a utility pole, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities ruled the death a suicide. Despite the cold weather, the man was 
wearing khaki shorts, a light jacket and sneakers. The man, believed to be a 
Mexican national, was carrying no identification. His pockets were empty, and 
he left no note, police said. A coroner's official who asked to remain 
anonymous said that the man was identified through his fingerprints, which were 
on file. 
</P>
