<P>
NATIONAL CEMETERY ONE-THIRD FINISHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction is about one-third finished on the new national cemetery being 
developed in the western San Joaquin Valley. When completed, the $10.5-million 
cemetery in rolling hills northwest of Los Banos will mark the first time 
graves have been readily accessible for Northern California veterans in nearly 
three decades. Golden Gate National Cemetery near San Francisco ran out of room 
in 1962 but still has space for cremated remains, said Dennis P. Gura, director 
of the new facility. 
</P>
