<P>
$20,000 COLLECTED FOR SURVIVORS OF DEADLY FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WESTLAND, Mich. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than $20,000 has been donated to survivors of a fire over the weekend that 
killed a man and six of his nine children, officials said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
"It's coming in faster than we can count," said Tom Keilman, a police chaplain. 
</P>
<P>
Fire officials said the Saturday night blaze apparently was ignited by a fallen 
Christmas tree. The father, Martin Dell'Orco, 38, at first escaped the blaze, 
but he died after re-entering the burning house. 
</P>
