<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO LA HABRA RETAIL STORES ARE HIT BY ARMED ROBBERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LA HABRA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police were searching for a man with an Uzi machine gun who held up a local 
sporting goods store Monday evening and may also have robbed a shoe store just 
a few miles away. 
</P>
<P>
Shortly after 7 p.m., a man confronted a clerk at a Big 5 sporting goods store 
at 1610 W. Whittier Blvd. with what appeared to be an Uzi machine gun and 
demanded money, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The man fled with an unknown amount of cash, said La Habra Police Sgt. Kevin 
Rayisch. He was not spotted again. 
</P>
<P>
Shortly before 6 p.m., a Payless shoe store at 1400 West Imperial Highway in La 
Habra was also hit by a robber. 
</P>
<P>
In that holdup, a man took some items to the cash register and, when asked how 
he would be paying, produced a revolver and demanded cash. He got away with an 
unknown amount of money and was seen driving off in a gray or green two-door 
sedan. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported in either robbery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
