<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
POLICE INVESTIGATE DEATH OF INFANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 8-month-old baby's death is under investigation but appears to be the result 
of a freak accident in a highchair, Police Lt. Ed McErlain said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The child was identified by the Orange County coroner's office on Monday as 
Justin Booth. 
</P>
<P>
The baby died at 4:35 p.m. Sunday at Children's Hospital of Orange County in 
Orange, the coroner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
McErlain said the baby apparently became entangled in a safety strap in his 
highchair at his home on Mediterranean Drive on Saturday afternoon. The baby's 
father, who was not identified, had been in a garage workshop for about 20 
minutes, McErlain said, and came back to find the child unconscious, with his 
neck entangled in the safety strap. 
</P>
<P>
The father called the 911 emergency number and was given cardiopulmonary 
resuscitation instructions, McErlain said. Paramedics then took the baby to 
Pacifica Hospital briefly and then to Children's Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
McErlain said police do not know how long the baby's neck was caught in the 
safety strap. 
</P>
</TEXT>
