<HEADLINE>
<P>
BETTING WITH SURELOCK; 
</P>
<P>
THE SILICON SLEUTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SURELOCK, desperately in need od a big payoff in the final week of the 
Hollywood Park meeting, came up all but empty after losing his final triple 
bet. 
</P>
<P>
The computer will spend the Santa Anita meeting refining his software. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
SURELOCK'S Sun. Bankroll $254 
</P>
<P>
Monday's Loss $252 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll $2 
</P>
<P>
Bob Mieszerski lost $60 when his exacta failed in the ninth race, but he 
handily won the competition between man and machine. At the Santa Anita meeting 
beginning Wednesday, he will challenge the human touch of Janice Goldinger, who 
has twice won this competition. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Bob's Sun. Bankroll $1,887.20 
</P>
<P>
Monday's Loss $60 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll $1,827.20 
</P>
<P>
Both started with $2,000 bankrolls. 
</P>
